						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1356, Pramādīcha, Māgha, śu. 10, Gu[ruvāra],</hi> probably corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1434 January 20, Wednesday,</hi> not Thursday. It refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Dēvarāya-Mahārāya</hi> and records that the king made a gift of a (village ?) to <hi rend="bold">Rāmayya,</hi> manager of the temple of god <hi rend="bold">Hanumantadēva</hi> set up by <hi rend="bold">[Sā]ḷuva-Śaṅkara[dēva ?].</hi></p>						

